---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Anshuman Singh — developer and independent researcher across software engineering, AI, physics, and mathematics."
>
  <Header />

  <main id="main-content" class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-serif font-semibold">About</h1>

    <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6 items-start">
      <img
        src="/profile-photo.jpg"
        alt="Photo of Anshuman Singh"
        width="140"
        height="140"
        class="rounded-full border border-border object-cover w-32 h-32 sm:w-36 sm:h-36 shrink-0"
      />
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-medium">Anshuman Singh</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted mt-1">Self-taught developer · Independent researcher · Based in Uttar Pradesh, India</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 prose prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p>
        I'm Anshuman Singh, a self-taught developer who started coding in 2023 and has been
        building things — mostly out of curiosity — ever since. Most of my work happens on
        Python: full-stack web development, backend systems, and applied AI/ML, alongside an
        ongoing personal interest in physics and mathematics that has nothing to do with any
        job and everything to do with genuinely wanting to understand how things work.
      </p>

      <p>
        A lot of my development happens in unconventional conditions — I build primarily on
        Termux, on Android, deploying to platforms like Render, PythonAnywhere, GitHub Pages,
        and InfinityFree. It's not the setup most tutorials assume, which has made me fairly
        stubborn about writing code that's simple to reason about and doesn't depend on a
        heavyweight local environment to work on.
      </p>

      <p>
        This journal exists because building things quietly and never writing any of it down
        felt like a waste of the actual learning. Every build log, research note, and
        reflection here is an honest record — including the parts that failed — rather than a
        highlight reel written to impress on first read.
      </p>

      <h2>What I Write About</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Engineering</strong> — Python, Flask, APIs, databases, full-stack web development</li>
        <li><strong>AI &amp; ML</strong> — machine learning concepts, LLMs, embeddings, applied AI projects</li>
        <li><strong>Research</strong> — physics, mathematics, and small computational experiments</li>
        <li><strong>Projects</strong> — build logs and case studies from things I'm actively building</li>
        <li><strong>Learning</strong> — honest reflections on books, courses, and concepts I'm working through</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What This Journal Isn't</h2>
      <p>
        It isn't a portfolio optimized to look impressive, and it isn't a place I claim
        credentials, employers, or achievements I don't have. What's here is what I've actually
        built and actually learned — nothing inflated, nothing borrowed.
      </p>

      <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/anshumanhq" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub — github.com/anshuman365</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://anshumanhq.github.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Main Website — anshumanhq.github.io</a></li>
        <li>
          LinkedIn —
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/anshuman-singh-662183303" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            linkedin.com/in/anshuman-singh-662183303
          </a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
